Saathy Backend
Human + AI Companionship Platform Backend
The Saathy Backend is the core infrastructure powering AI companionship, human listener support, emotional memory, journaling, daily check-ins, safety monitoring, and continuity experiences.
The primary objective of the backend is not message delivery.
The primary objective is emotional continuity.

Backend at a Glance
Current Tech Stack

Core Backend
- Node.js (API orchestration)
- FastAPI (AI services)

Database & Storage
- Supabase PostgreSQL
- Redis (Caching)

AI
- OpenRouter
- Gemini / OpenAI Models

 Realtime Communication
- LiveKit

 Payments
- Razorpay 

 User Journey

Step 1: User Authentication
User signs up or logs in through Supabase Authentication.


Step 2: AI Conversation
User starts chatting with Saathy.
User Message
 ↓
Node.js Backend
 ↓
Safety Check
 ↓
Memory Retrieval
 ↓
AI Processing
 ↓
Response
Step 3: Memory Formation
Important details are extracted and stored.
This enables future continuity. 
Step 4: Daily Pulse
User receives emotional check-ins.
Examples:
Mood
Energy
Stress
Loneliness
Trends are stored and analyzed over time.
Step 5: Human Listener Support
When required:
User
 ↓
Matching Engine
 ↓
Available Listener
 ↓
Voice / Video Session
Step 6: Safety Monitoring
Every interaction passes through safety systems.
